       fhir:ElementDefinition.short [ fhir:value "When medication should be administered" ] ;
       fhir:ElementDefinition.definition [ fhir:value "When medication should be administered." ] ;
       fhir:ElementDefinition.comment [ fhir:value "This attribute might not always be populated while the Dosage.text is expected to be populated.  If both are populated, then the Dosage.text should reflect the content of the Dosage.timing." ] ;
       fhir:ElementDefinition.requirements [ fhir:value "The timing schedule for giving the medication to the patient. This  data type allows many different expressions. For example: \"Every 8 hours\"; \"Three times a day\"; \"1/2 an hour before breakfast for 10 days from 23-Dec 2011:\"; \"15 Oct 2013, 17 Oct 2013 and 1 Nov 2013\".  Sometimes, a rate can imply duration when expressed as total volume / duration (e.g.  500mL/2 hours implies a duration of 2 hours).  However, when rate doesn't imply duration (e.g. 250mL/hour), then the timing.repeat.duration is needed to convey the infuse over time period." ] ;
